history.content: some u-grad classes rely heavily on topics from 61c. you want to avoid those until you've finished it (161, 162). 168, 169, 17* if you like theory, and 186 (though reputed to be a bit boring) are all good choices. Any of the 194 classes are interesting too

children.subject:
DS100 or EE126/127 is also good if you're eventually gonna take 189. 

100 in particular has a good workload to pair with 61C. Can't speak to the others
